def: "Residual sugars in fermented ciders (diluted 1,600 to 4,000 fold with HPLC grade water) were measured on an ion chromatograph (Dionex(TM) ICS-5000 fitted with an ED50 amperometric detector. Sunnyvale, CA) using a 25 ul sample loop and CarboPac PA1 guard (4 mm x 50 mm; P/N 0309) and CarboPac analytical (4 mm x 250 mm; P/N 035391) columns. Samples were injected into filtered and degassed 200 mM NaOH eluant carrier at 1 ml/min. Sugar concentrations were calculated with Dionex Chromeleon(TM) 7 software using a seven-point standard curve with a polynomial fit in the range of 1.25- 40 mg/g (Sorbitol and Glucose) and 2.5-80 mg/g (Fructose and Sucrose)" []
is_a: CIDER:0000017 ! Variables
